    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-02T13:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-02T13:30:00-05:00" n="77"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856B.20/41: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-02T14:00:00-04:30"
                            >February 2, 1942—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. Department’s 76, January 31, 9 p.m. Following Department’s instruction I saw
                    President Medina last night. He was mollified by the President’s personal
                    message and the assurance given. He expects therefore that the formula for
                    Venezuelan participation will be obtained before he has to face publicity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
